<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6638] Remove unnecessary use of reflection in SignatureChecker</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6638</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ca line 377 in SignatureChecker we use reflection to call DatabaseMetaData#getFunctionColumns. This is no longer necessary after we removed support for JDR 169.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;blue&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Update:&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; There are more occurrences of reflection that can be removed in this class.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
